710073f-b.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 14th Street (West)
710073f-b.text:
Eighth Avenue, south from W. 14th Street, as photographed from
atop the Port Authority Building at No. 111 Eighth Avenue. The tri-
angular park shown is Jackson Square. This is one block to the south
of 14th Street and is bounded by 8th Avenue, Greenwich Avenue and
Horatio Street. The tall apartment building there is at the S. W.
corner of the last two thoroughfares and is identified as No. 2
Horatio Street.
April 26, 1933
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
NO REERODUCTIONS

710072f-b.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 14th Street (West)
710072f-b.text:
Eighth Avenue, west side, north from 4. 14th to 15th Streets.
Shown at the N. W. corner of 14th Street is the New York Savings
Bank. View 3 is limited to this structure. No. 2 is photographed
from atop the apartment house, No. 2 Horatio Street. It includes
the New York Port Authority Building as a backdrop. On the right
is the towering County Trust Building. This structure stands on
the cleared site shown in the right foreground of View 1. Additional
construction shown is for a new subway.
View 1: May 30, 1929
View 2r March 16, 1933
View 3: February 14, 1932
P. L. Snerr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
